in less than ten minutes.

445
00:26:14,823 --> 00:26:16,116
Oh.

446
00:26:17,451 --> 00:26:21,663
I take back every single bad thing
I've been saying about you.

447
00:26:23,290 --> 00:26:24,499
To myself.

448
00:26:25,709 --> 00:26:26,710
In private.

449
00:26:30,672 --> 00:26:32,341
Four years ago,

450
00:26:33,217 --> 00:26:34,468
we were dreamers.

451
00:26:36,178 --> 00:26:38,680
<i>Back then, the unknown meant adventure,</i>

452
00:26:40,307 --> 00:26:42,976
<i>and mystery, and discovery.</i>

453
00:26:45,395 --> 00:26:49,233
<i>With space, the greatest mystery of all.</i>

454
00:26:49,316 --> 00:26:51,043
<i>The last occasion</i>
<i>led to the accident</i>

455
00:26:51,067 --> 00:26:53,320
<i>that mutated them
and gave them those fan...</i>

456
00:27:01,286 --> 00:27:02,912
<i>What we learned</i>

457
00:27:02,996 --> 00:27:05,457
<i>was that the unknown also meant fear.</i>

458
00:27:07,501 --> 00:27:11,004
<i>And profound, radical change.</i>

459
00:27:20,264 --> 00:27:21,556
Hiya, pal.

460
00:27:21,640 --> 00:27:23,642
Johnny showed me the new suit.

461
00:27:23,725 --> 00:27:26,811
It's pretty spiffy,
especially compared to the old ones.

462
00:27:26,895 --> 00:27:28,188
Well, the old ones...

463
00:27:30,607 --> 00:27:32,108
