464
00:27:32,192 --> 00:27:33,360
Eh, who could've known?

465
00:27:34,110 --> 00:27:35,195
Me.

466
00:27:36,488 --> 00:27:38,698
- I could've known.
- Stop.

467
00:27:38,782 --> 00:27:41,951
Please. You gotta stop
beating yourself up about this.

468
00:27:43,578 --> 00:27:46,956
You know, Stretch, I got bad news for you.

469
00:27:47,957 --> 00:27:49,418
You ain't that smart.

470
00:27:49,501 --> 00:27:51,002
Except I am that smart.

471
00:27:51,085 --> 00:27:52,504
Oh, yeah? Can you cook?

472
00:27:53,380 --> 00:27:55,299
It's more of an art, not a science.

473
00:27:55,382 --> 00:27:56,484
Did you pass your driver's test?

474
00:27:56,508 --> 00:27:58,302
That was due to poorly marked signage.

475
00:27:58,385 --> 00:28:00,637
Huh.

476
00:28:02,055 --> 00:28:05,225
This Galactus, this herald,

477
00:28:05,309 --> 00:28:07,519
they got no idea what they're up against.

478
00:28:09,604 --> 00:28:12,982
So the four of us will return to space
and face the danger waiting there,

479
00:28:14,693 --> 00:28:17,237
<i>and we will find this Galactus.</i>

480
00:28:17,862 --> 00:28:20,300
<i>The second the engines fire,</i>
<i>everything you do from then on</i>

481
00:28:20,324 --> 00:28:24,077
will be the first time a pregnant woman
has done them in the history of the world.

482
00:28:25,412 --> 00:28:26,413
I know.

483
00:28:28,790 --> 00:28:30,083
I really do.

484
00:28:32,711 --> 00:28:35,914
And just because I'm not talking about it
doesn't mean I'm not thinking about it.

485
00:28:38,342 --> 00:28:39,426
About him.

486
00:28:43,847 --> 00:28:45,890
I really love my new suit.

487
00:28:45,974 --> 00:28:48,352
It's really your old one,
it's just a lot bigger.

488
00:28:50,312 --> 00:28:51,438
Bluer.

489
00:28:51,521 --> 00:28:52,897
It is actually bluer.

490
00:28:52,981 --> 00:28:55,442
Just a little extra
around the sides is all.

491
00:28:55,525 --> 00:28:57,694
<i>This is </i>Excelsior <i>Launch Control.</i>

492
00:28:57,777 --> 00:29:00,655
<i>T-minus two hours,
37 minutes, 20 seconds.</i>

493
00:29:01,615 --> 00:29:06,035
<i>Here we stand</i>
<i>prepared to face a danger that is unknown.</i>

494
00:29:11,875 --> 00:29:14,002
<i>A danger that
has threatened our home,</i>

495
00:29:15,545 --> 00:29:17,005
<i>threatened our families</i>

496
00:29:18,757 --> 00:29:20,759
<i>and threatened this planet.</i>

497
00:29:24,679 --> 00:29:27,432
<i>The unknown will become known,</i>

498
00:29:27,516 --> 00:29:29,142
<i>and we will protect you.</i>

499
00:29:30,184 --> 00:29:31,561
We will protect you.

500
00:29:48,119 --> 00:29:49,788
Final check and check, please.

501
00:29:50,747 --> 00:29:52,457
- Check.
- Check.

502
00:29:52,541 --> 00:29:54,000
Check.

503
00:29:54,083 --> 00:29:56,753
<i>Twelve, eleven,</i>

504
00:29:57,629 --> 00:30:03,134
<i>ten, nine, eight, seven...</i>

505
00:30:03,217 --> 00:30:04,678
Starting ignition sequence.

506
00:30:06,137 --> 00:30:09,558
<i>six, five, four, three...</i>

507
00:30:09,641 --> 00:30:10,850
Go for launch.

508
00:30:10,934 --> 00:30:13,478
<i>two, one.</i>

509
00:30:29,953 --> 00:30:31,913
<i>The </i>Excelsior <i>has liftoff.</i>

510
00:30:47,596 --> 00:30:49,723
Whoo-hoo!

511
00:30:55,103 --> 00:30:57,146
<i>Ladies and gentlemen,</i>

512
00:30:57,230 --> 00:30:59,232
<i>we have a successful launch.</i>

513
00:31:03,737 --> 00:31:05,447
<i>And from all of us on Earth,</i>

514
00:31:06,197 --> 00:31:07,699
<i>we wish you good luck.</i>

515
00:31:08,366 --> 00:31:09,534
<i>And Godspeed.</i>

516
00:31:11,244 --> 00:31:12,370
Thank you, Earth.

517
00:31:18,543 --> 00:31:19,753
You seeing that?

518
00:31:23,465 --> 00:31:25,299
Approaching the FTL engine.

519
00:31:40,231 --> 00:31:41,483
Wait for my signal, Sue.

520
00:31:41,566 --> 00:31:42,567
Yeah.

521
00:31:42,651 --> 00:31:46,571
And three, two, one. Mark.

522
00:31:54,996 --> 00:31:58,917
And we are locked.

523
00:32:00,251 --> 00:32:02,546
And clear for FTL navigation.

524
00:32:02,629 --> 00:32:06,841
Faster-than-light in three, two, one.

525
00:32:18,728 --> 00:32:21,105
So the herald's
energy signature tracks

526
00:32:21,189 --> 00:32:23,357
to this binary system here.

527
00:32:23,441 --> 00:32:26,069
LHS-275, yes.

528
00:32:26,570 --> 00:32:29,072
Where we find her, we find Galactus.

529
00:32:29,155 --> 00:32:30,990
Reed, what are we up against here?

530
00:32:31,074 --> 00:32:33,577
Some sort of a space dragon
or something?

531
00:32:33,660 --> 00:32:35,244
- Cool.
- We don't know.

532
00:32:35,328 --> 00:32:36,621
But it's basic tactical science.

533
00:32:36,705 --> 00:32:39,415
Observe, assess capabilities,
have H.E.R.B.I.E. collect

534
00:32:39,499 --> 00:32:40,750
any liquid, gas...

535
00:32:40,834 --> 00:32:42,126
solid materials,

536
00:32:42,210 --> 00:32:43,545
analyze his physiology.

537
00:32:45,880 --> 00:32:49,425
Look, if he's just some big guy in a ship,
then yes, you can punch him out.

538
00:33:00,645 --> 00:33:02,897
Coming in on the dark side
of the system's larger planet.

539
00:33:02,981 --> 00:33:05,233
Copy that. I'm gonna take us out of FTL.

540
00:33:05,316 --> 00:33:07,235
Okay, everyone. Be prepared.

541
00:33:14,033 --> 00:33:15,451
So, where's this Galactus?

542
00:33:20,289 --> 00:33:21,499
That's strange.

543
00:33:22,291 --> 00:33:25,419
The herald's heat signature
is coming from inside the planet.

544
00:33:30,174 --> 00:33:32,093
What the hell is happening to that planet?

545
00:33:32,176 --> 00:33:33,637
Is there something alive down there?

546
00:33:45,064 --> 00:33:46,357
What is that?

547
00:33:48,610 --> 00:33:50,153
- Ben!
- I'm on it!

548
00:33:50,236 --> 00:33:52,155
Dropping us out of FTL.

549
00:33:56,660 --> 00:33:57,786
Watch out!

550
00:34:03,082 --> 00:34:04,167
Sue, hide us!

551
00:34:22,518 --> 00:34:25,313
It's all gone. The whole planet.

552
00:34:25,396 --> 00:34:27,649
And it was 13% larger than Earth.

553
00:34:33,738 --> 00:34:34,799
- Ben!
- It's not responding.

554
00:34:34,823 --> 00:34:35,824
I'm locked out.

555
00:34:37,951 --> 00:34:40,620
H.E.R.B.I.E.,
try to stabilize the engines.

556
00:34:42,413 --> 00:34:43,247
What's going on?

557
00:34:43,331 --> 00:34:45,249
It's got us. It's pulling us in.

558
00:34:45,333 --> 00:34:46,960
Ben, save the engines.

559
00:34:48,127 --> 00:34:49,378
Save the engine!

560
00:35:23,579 --> 00:35:24,580
Johnny...

561
00:35:26,750 --> 00:35:28,084
your girlfriend's back.

562
00:35:39,679 --> 00:35:40,847
Hi.

563
00:35:41,472 --> 00:35:43,141
Galactus will see you.

564
00:35:43,641 --> 00:35:45,685
- I'll go.
- All of you.

565
00:35:47,812 --> 00:35:49,188
You should not have come.

566
00:36:29,187 --> 00:36:30,479
Follow.

567
00:36:31,605 --> 00:36:33,250
Scan everything
and collect samples.

568
00:36:46,079 --> 00:36:47,538
What does Galactus want?

569
00:36:48,915 --> 00:36:51,625
He doesn't want. He feeds.

570
00:36:53,795 --> 00:36:56,172
How does he choose
which planets to consume?

571
00:36:56,714 --> 00:36:58,216
He does not.

572
00:37:00,051 --> 00:37:01,344
You choose.

573
00:37:02,762 --> 00:37:03,763
Yes.

574
00:37:06,891 --> 00:37:08,935
Uh, Johnny. What are you doing?

575
00:37:09,477 --> 00:37:10,854
I'm gonna charm her.

576
00:37:14,941 --> 00:37:16,150
So what did you say to me?

577
00:37:16,901 --> 00:37:18,569
When you threw me off your board?

578
00:37:19,821 --> 00:37:20,989
What did you say?

579
00:37:24,909 --> 00:37:26,077
It's a blessing.

580
00:37:26,786 --> 00:37:29,956
It means, "Die with yours."

581
00:37:31,457 --> 00:37:33,501
"Die with yours."

582
00:37:35,669 --> 00:37:36,838
Last question.

583
00:37:36,921 --> 00:37:38,756
So the surfboard, right?

584
00:37:38,840 --> 00:37:40,466
Is that part of your body? Or is that...

585
00:37:49,183 --> 00:37:50,518
So she dumped you already?

586
00:37:50,601 --> 00:37:51,644
No. It went well.

587
00:38:07,493 --> 00:38:09,954
You stand before Galactus.

588
00:38:18,629 --> 00:38:21,465
The Devourer of Worlds honors you.

589
00:38:32,018 --> 00:38:33,227
We are honored.

590
00:38:34,938 --> 00:38:38,149
I was once little like you.

591
00:38:38,900 --> 00:38:41,402
Billions of years ago.

592
00:38:42,195 --> 00:38:44,738
A man from another world

593
00:38:45,656 --> 00:38:50,661
before this relentless, eternal hunger.

594
00:38:54,665 --> 00:38:56,667
You have traveled far.

595
00:38:59,337 --> 00:39:00,671
Yes.

596
00:39:03,382 --> 00:39:06,010
To beg for mercy.

597
00:39:07,971 --> 00:39:09,388
To talk.

598
00:39:10,306 --> 00:39:13,977
You carry the power to save your world.

599
00:39:14,060 --> 00:39:15,519
Yes. I believe we do.

600
00:39:16,312 --> 00:39:17,813
Inside her.

601
00:39:19,065 --> 00:39:20,399
The child.

602
00:39:23,069 --> 00:39:24,237
- What the hell?
- What...

603
00:39:24,778 --> 00:39:26,614
He hungers.

604
00:39:26,697 --> 00:39:28,116
What does that mean?

605
00:39:28,199 --> 00:39:30,784
I will spare your world.

606
00:39:31,660 --> 00:39:33,454
In exchange for the boy.

607
00:39:33,537 --> 00:39:35,873
What? No.

608
00:39:36,415 --> 00:39:39,293
He possesses the Power Cosmic,

609
00:39:39,377 --> 00:39:42,671
and he will inherit this cursed throne.

610
00:39:43,631 --> 00:39:46,300
It's not true. He's... He's normal.

611
00:39:46,384 --> 00:39:49,553
We would know. I would know.
I tested the child.

612
00:39:49,637 --> 00:39:52,681
- He hides his nature from you.
- No.

613
00:40:03,692 --> 00:40:04,902
What are you doing to her?

614
00:40:04,986 --> 00:40:07,071
Baby's coming.
The baby's coming.

615
00:40:07,155 --> 00:40:08,364
- Now?
- Yeah.

616
00:40:08,447 --> 00:40:10,408
You will not have our planet.

617
00:40:11,117 --> 00:40:12,994
And you will never have our son!

618
00:40:22,086 --> 00:40:25,298
I will eat your planet slowly

619
00:40:25,881 --> 00:40:28,551
while your child watches.

620
00:40:55,036 --> 00:40:56,162
No you don't!

621
00:41:06,797 --> 00:41:08,007
I'm coming, buddy!

622
00:41:10,218 --> 00:41:11,219
Go, go, go, go!

623
00:41:12,303 --> 00:41:14,888
H.E.R.B.I.E., prep all systems
for immediate launch.

624
00:41:21,020 --> 00:41:23,481
No!

625
00:41:30,113 --> 00:41:31,572
No!

626
00:41:36,619 --> 00:41:39,330
Surfboard, not part of the body.

627
00:41:48,922 --> 00:41:50,424
Come on.

628
00:42:03,896 --> 00:42:04,897
H.E.R.B.I.E.!

629
00:42:04,980 --> 00:42:06,232
Come on.

630
00:42:09,110 --> 00:42:10,319
Get us out of here, Ben!

631
00:42:10,403 --> 00:42:12,405
Hang in there, Suze, I'll get you home.

632
00:42:28,254 --> 00:42:29,422
Get us to the FTL!

633
00:42:30,964 --> 00:42:32,258
FTL in visual range.

634
00:42:32,341 --> 00:42:34,843
- Babe.
- I'm here, Sue. I'm here.

635
00:42:37,054 --> 00:42:38,514
Surfer on our six.

636
00:42:39,432 --> 00:42:40,849
Attach then jump.

637
00:42:40,933 --> 00:42:43,477
- And go where?
- Anywhere! Just jump!

638
00:42:47,565 --> 00:42:49,709
H.E.R.B.I.E., I'm gonna need your help
stabilizing this thing.

639
00:43:00,369 --> 00:43:02,079
Hold on!

640
00:43:12,340 --> 00:43:14,592
Ben!

641
00:43:22,475 --> 00:43:24,352
We lost her. All clear.

642
00:43:31,484 --> 00:43:32,651
She's still on us.

643
00:43:32,735 --> 00:43:33,736
Johnny, kill her.

644
00:43:34,278 --> 00:43:35,112
- Really?
- Yeah.

645
00:43:35,196 --> 00:43:36,572
She wants to take your nephew.

646
00:43:36,655 --> 00:43:38,616
- Kill her!
- All right. All right.

647
00:43:40,784 --> 00:43:44,372
Just when I finally met
someone interesting.

648
00:43:53,839 --> 00:43:55,466
It's bending the beam!

649
00:43:55,549 --> 00:43:57,885
The wormhole is bending the beam!

650
00:44:03,349 --> 00:44:05,643
Reed, I can't get a lock on her!

651
00:44:05,726 --> 00:44:07,311
All right. Figure it out. Come on.

652
00:44:07,395 --> 00:44:08,604
Reed, what's the plan?

653
00:44:17,446 --> 00:44:18,590
Johnny, quit screwing around.

654
00:44:18,614 --> 00:44:22,201
Do I tell you how to drive the ship?
Don't tell me how to kill sexy aliens!

655
00:44:22,285 --> 00:44:23,702
Stop calling her sexy.

656
00:44:28,249 --> 00:44:30,293
- Oh!
- Yes! Yes!

657
00:44:30,376 --> 00:44:31,377
- Yes!
- Yes!

658
00:44:37,550 --> 00:44:38,551
She's back!

659
00:44:38,592 --> 00:44:40,553
- Reed, I can't shake her.
- Working on it!

660
00:44:42,221 --> 00:44:44,139
- She's slippery!
- Reed!

661
00:44:48,644 --> 00:44:49,978
Drop us out of FTL here.

662
00:44:50,479 --> 00:44:52,189
That's a pretty big neutron star.

663
00:44:52,273 --> 00:44:53,941
I know. We're gonna use it.

664
00:44:54,024 --> 00:44:55,859
Isn't that basically a black hole?

665
00:44:56,485 --> 00:44:57,486
Won't that kill us?

666
00:44:57,570 --> 00:44:58,737
Taking us out.

667
00:45:18,341 --> 00:45:19,425
What's the plan?

668
00:45:19,508 --> 00:45:22,595
Draw her close enough to the star,
she'll get stuck in the gravity well.

669
00:45:22,678 --> 00:45:24,137
There'll be a time dilation.

670
00:45:24,221 --> 00:45:26,307
- How much of a dilation?
- Is it more than mine?

671
00:45:26,390 --> 00:45:28,016
It'll take her a month to break free.

672
00:45:29,893 --> 00:45:31,061
Take us in, Ben.

673
00:45:31,144 --> 00:45:32,813
Reed, we could get sucked in.

674
00:45:33,439 --> 00:45:34,565
Ben, trust me.

675
00:45:35,232 --> 00:45:36,275
Hang on.

676
00:45:50,706 --> 00:45:51,790
Come on.

677
00:45:51,874 --> 00:45:52,875
It's chewing us up!

678
00:45:54,042 --> 00:45:55,127
Get closer.

679
00:45:55,210 --> 00:45:56,462
It's chewing us up!

680
00:45:56,545 --> 00:45:58,171
A little closer!

681
00:45:58,881 --> 00:46:00,442
Come on, Reed. What are we doing?

682
00:46:00,466 --> 00:46:04,052
Sue, we need 30 seconds of invisibility.
Can you do it?

683
00:46:04,136 --> 00:46:05,929
After your next contraction.

684
00:46:54,353 --> 00:46:55,938
- Yes!
- Hell, yeah!

685
00:46:56,021 --> 00:46:59,567
You all right, Sue?

686
00:47:00,484 --> 00:47:01,944
We need to strap you down.

687
00:47:02,027 --> 00:47:04,447
- Strapping her down.
- Do not strap me down!

688
00:47:05,448 --> 00:47:06,949
Not strapping her down.

689
00:47:07,032 --> 00:47:08,659
Baby...

690
00:47:08,742 --> 00:47:10,411
- What?
- you need gravity to push.

691
00:47:10,494 --> 00:47:11,787
This is not right.

692
00:47:11,870 --> 00:47:13,097
It's not how it's supposed to be.

693
00:47:13,121 --> 00:47:14,415
I know, I know.

694
00:47:14,498 --> 00:47:15,791
But we're gonna make it work.

695
00:47:17,418 --> 00:47:18,919
You're doing wonderful, my love.

696
00:47:22,339 --> 00:47:24,341
We don't have enough juice
to get home.

697
00:47:24,425 --> 00:47:25,759
Oh, no.

698
00:47:29,513 --> 00:47:30,556
No, we do not.

699
00:47:30,639 --> 00:47:34,059
I could slingshot around the star,
draft off its orbital momentum.

700
00:47:34,142 --> 00:47:36,562
We need to get to
.88 speed of light.

701
00:47:36,645 --> 00:47:38,271
Reed!

702
00:47:38,355 --> 00:47:39,982
- Johnny, the velocity gauge.
- Reed!

703
00:47:40,065 --> 00:47:41,066
On it.

704
00:47:42,067 --> 00:47:43,777
- Oh, don't... don't go.
- I'm here.

705
00:47:43,861 --> 00:47:45,404
- I'm not going anywhere.
- Don't go.

706
00:47:45,488 --> 00:47:47,114
I'm right here.

707
00:47:47,197 --> 00:47:49,199
Beginning slingshot. Here we go.

708
00:47:52,077 --> 00:47:53,454
Coming up on .82.

709
00:47:53,537 --> 00:47:54,663
On your mark, Johnny.

710
00:47:56,457 --> 00:47:57,958
Why... Why do they wanna take him?

711
00:47:58,041 --> 00:47:59,102
Something is wrong with him.

712
00:47:59,126 --> 00:47:59,960
There's nothing wrong with him.

713
00:48:00,043 --> 00:48:01,688
- You don't know that.
- Yes, I do. I do know.

714
00:48:01,712 --> 00:48:03,648
No, you don't. You know everything,
but you don't know that.

715
00:48:03,672 --> 00:48:05,434
- What if he's a monster?
- He's not a monster.

716
00:48:06,258 --> 00:48:08,340
- Everything's gonna change.
- Nothing is gonna change.

717
00:48:08,385 --> 00:48:10,067
- Everything's gonna change.
- I promise you.

718
00:48:10,095 --> 00:48:11,805
- I promise.
- You can't promise that.

719
00:48:11,889 --> 00:48:13,348
- I promise.
- You can't promise that.

720
00:48:13,432 --> 00:48:14,975
- Reed...
- Okay.

721
00:48:19,187 --> 00:48:20,981
He's coming. He's coming.

722
00:48:21,064 --> 00:48:22,107
Give me your hand.

723
00:48:22,190 --> 00:48:23,316
.84. Ben!

724
00:48:23,400 --> 00:48:24,735
Come on!

725
00:48:27,404 --> 00:48:28,989
- Sue? Push.
- No.

726
00:48:29,072 --> 00:48:30,658
- Yes, you can.
- .85.

727
00:48:30,741 --> 00:48:31,825
- Ready?
- Okay.

728
00:48:31,909 --> 00:48:34,411
One, two, three, push!

729
00:48:37,915 --> 00:48:40,417
- Come on!
- .86!

730
00:48:40,501 --> 00:48:42,753
Push. Push. That's good.

731
00:48:44,254 --> 00:48:45,297
.87.

732
00:48:48,884 --> 00:48:50,385
- Mark!
- Ben!

733
00:48:50,469 --> 00:48:52,220
H.E.R.B.I.E.

734
00:48:53,681 --> 00:48:55,223
Ben, help!

735
00:48:55,766 --> 00:48:57,184
Thrusters engaged.

736
00:48:58,727 --> 00:49:00,103
H.E.R.B.I.E., get ready!

737
00:49:05,943 --> 00:49:07,319
Hold on, everyone.

738
00:49:32,260 --> 00:49:35,013
I got you, little guy.

739
00:50:05,961 --> 00:50:06,962
Franklin.

740
00:50:37,117 --> 00:50:39,369
There! There! Come on. I see it!

741
00:50:48,545 --> 00:50:49,838
Wow!

742
00:51:08,440 --> 00:51:10,525
<i>After a month long return trip,</i>

743
00:51:10,609 --> 00:51:12,778
<i>the Fantastic Four are finally home</i>

744
00:51:12,861 --> 00:51:15,072
<i>and receiving a warm welcome.</i>

745
00:51:27,500 --> 00:51:29,795
Oh, my God. Unbelievable.

746
00:51:29,878 --> 00:51:31,880
- Lynne, we're going to need...
- Come this way.

747
00:51:35,718 --> 00:51:37,320
- Reed! Reed!
- Move back!

748
00:51:37,344 --> 00:51:39,847
Dr. Richards,
over here! Can we get a word?

749
00:51:39,930 --> 00:51:42,015
Stand back. Make a path.

750
00:51:42,099 --> 00:51:44,559
Sue! Sue!

751
00:51:49,022 --> 00:51:50,941
They're ready for you. Step up.

752
00:51:51,024 --> 00:51:52,025
Just keep it brief.

753
00:51:56,822 --> 00:51:58,907
I'm sorry. We don't have
a prepared statement.

754
00:52:02,035 --> 00:52:04,204
One at a time, please. One at a time.

755
00:52:04,287 --> 00:52:05,330
Connor.

756
00:52:05,831 --> 00:52:06,832
Welcome back.

757
00:52:06,915 --> 00:52:09,084
Could you take us through
how you defeated Galactus?

758
00:52:10,794 --> 00:52:11,795
How we de...

759
00:52:15,215 --> 00:52:16,299
We didn't.

760
00:52:16,383 --> 00:52:19,052
Not yet. Not yet, we didn't.

761
00:52:19,136 --> 00:52:20,196
What does that mean?

762
00:52:20,220 --> 00:52:21,680
Uh, follow up!

763
00:52:23,766 --> 00:52:25,142
What do you mean, you didn't?

764
00:52:26,685 --> 00:52:29,855
We attempted to negotiate, but Galactus...

765
00:52:33,400 --> 00:52:35,819
He asked too high a price.

766
00:52:35,903 --> 00:52:38,155
- Well, what does he want?
- What did he ask?

767
00:52:42,200 --> 00:52:43,744
He asked for our child.

768
00:52:45,078 --> 00:52:46,163
What?

769
00:52:46,246 --> 00:52:48,791
He said, "Give us your child",

770
00:52:50,667 --> 00:52:52,044
"and I will spare the earth."

771
00:52:53,336 --> 00:52:55,672
We said no, obviously. We said no.

772
00:52:56,339 --> 00:52:59,927
We're gonna... We're gonna circle back
with a more detailed statement...

773
00:53:00,010 --> 00:53:01,720
- You said no?
- What does that mean for us?

774
00:53:01,804 --> 00:53:03,680
Could giving Galactus the child save us?

775
00:53:04,639 --> 00:53:06,934
- Whoa, whoa, whoa.
- Hang on... You can't just...

776
00:53:07,017 --> 00:53:09,019
Just answer this. Answer this.

777
00:53:09,853 --> 00:53:11,563
Are we safe?

778
00:53:12,605 --> 00:53:14,149
Are we safe?

779
00:53:18,028 --> 00:53:19,029
I don't know.

780
00:53:20,030 --> 00:53:21,573
What do you mean, you don't know?

781
00:53:21,656 --> 00:53:22,657
You don't know?

782
00:53:23,826 --> 00:53:25,994
What do you mean you don't know?

783
00:53:26,078 --> 00:53:27,537
What do you mean you don't know?

784
00:53:42,552 --> 00:53:45,973
I'm sorry. I've failed you.

785
00:53:46,723 --> 00:53:49,392
I need the child.

786
00:53:49,476 --> 00:53:52,104
I must get the child.

787
00:53:53,438 --> 00:53:55,148
But he's just a baby.

788
00:54:01,113 --> 00:54:04,741
He is a being of infinite power.

789
00:54:05,575 --> 00:54:09,454
One strong enough to absorb my hunger

790
00:54:10,580 --> 00:54:14,835
so that I may finally rest.

791
00:54:15,585 --> 00:54:18,022
- How much time do we even have?
- What do we do when he gets here?

792
00:54:18,046 --> 00:54:20,149
What about the ship?
We blast it. Problem solved.

793
00:54:20,173 --> 00:54:21,008
You can't blast it.

794
00:54:21,091 --> 00:54:22,675
Conventional weapons won't work.

795
00:54:22,759 --> 00:54:24,011
- So, we run.
- We run?

796
00:54:24,094 --> 00:54:26,263
Draw him away from Earth.
We're faster than him, right?

797
00:54:26,346 --> 00:54:28,157
- Not faster than the herald.
- We've got a head start.

798
00:54:28,181 --> 00:54:29,325
Yeah, but that's all we got.

799
00:54:29,349 --> 00:54:31,226
And then he could still
eat the Earth anyways.

800
00:54:31,977 --> 00:54:32,978
Reed?

801
00:54:33,979 --> 00:54:35,605
You wanna take us through what you have?

802
00:54:36,273 --> 00:54:38,358
- What I have?
- Yeah.

803
00:54:39,359 --> 00:54:40,777
What I have is nothing.

804
00:54:40,861 --> 00:54:42,487
Nothing. Did you say nothing?

805
00:54:42,570 --> 00:54:46,116
I analyzed the samples H.E.R.B.I.E. took
from Galactus's ship.

806
00:54:46,199 --> 00:54:49,828
All evidence suggests
he predates our universe, our reality.

807
00:54:49,912 --> 00:54:53,040
It could take ten years to understand
his composition, let alone his existence.

808
00:54:53,123 --> 00:54:54,374
You're talking about a god?

809
00:54:54,457 --> 00:54:57,460
I'm talking about something
beyond our experience.

810
00:54:57,544 --> 00:54:59,171
An unknowable life.

811
00:54:59,254 --> 00:55:01,256
Who imagines Franklin as his successor

812
00:55:01,339 --> 00:55:03,842
and possessing some kind of cosmic power.

813
00:55:03,926 --> 00:55:04,759
That can't be true.

814
00:55:04,843 --> 00:55:06,029
You ran all those tests. Right?

815
00:55:06,053 --> 00:55:08,263
I have, but I don't know
what can or cannot be.

816
00:55:08,346 --> 00:55:10,428
I'm not sure how long.
I'm not sure of anything. I...

817
00:55:10,974 --> 00:55:11,975
I have nothing. I...

818
00:55:12,684 --> 00:55:13,768
I have nothing.

819
00:55:15,562 --> 00:55:17,814
If we could solve something,

820
00:55:17,898 --> 00:55:21,276
any link in the chain...

821
00:55:22,194 --> 00:55:23,570
E is the effort force,

822
00:55:23,653 --> 00:55:25,335
R is the lever arm
connected to the effort.

823
00:55:25,405 --> 00:55:26,406
I is the load,

824
00:55:26,489 --> 00:55:28,091
r is the lever arm
connected to the load.

825
00:55:28,158 --> 00:55:30,243
Archimedes. The Law of Levers.

826
00:55:30,327 --> 00:55:33,580
"Give me a lever and a place to stand
and I will move the earth."

827
00:55:34,915 --> 00:55:35,916
We need a lever.

828
00:55:35,999 --> 00:55:37,500
You... You wanna translate that?

829
00:55:37,584 --> 00:55:40,587
Yeah, we solve the right small problem,
we solve the big Galactus one.

830
00:55:40,670 --> 00:55:42,130
Yes. Yes.

831
00:55:42,214 --> 00:55:44,091
All right, boys, let's go look for levers.

832
00:55:44,174 --> 00:55:45,175
Yep.

833
00:55:48,178 --> 00:55:50,889
You know, you're supposed to sleep
when the baby sleeps.

834
00:55:50,973 --> 00:55:53,475
I've been, uh, you know,
reading the books.

835
00:55:54,893 --> 00:55:57,312
He thinks the baby actually sleeps.

836
00:56:09,449 --> 00:56:10,993
I gotta show you something.

837
00:56:11,076 --> 00:56:12,117
What do you wanna show me?

838
00:56:12,160 --> 00:56:14,037
- It's really good.
- I barely slept last night.

839
00:56:14,121 --> 00:56:15,205
I'm sorry to hear that.

840
00:56:15,288 --> 00:56:16,724
It's not like you chose this whole thing.

841
00:56:16,748 --> 00:56:18,166
Being a mother, you know?

842
00:56:18,250 --> 00:56:20,132
Sit down. Good.
I gotta show you. Just trust me.

843
00:56:20,710 --> 00:56:22,212
Okay. All right.

844
00:56:22,295 --> 00:56:23,964
Johnny, it smells.

845
00:56:24,047 --> 00:56:25,882
It's pheromones. Relax. All right.

846
00:56:26,591 --> 00:56:28,051
Racking back the helmet cam.

847
00:56:34,432 --> 00:56:35,642
<i>It's a blessing.</i>

848
00:56:36,351 --> 00:56:38,770
<i>It means, "Die with yours."</i>

849
00:56:43,858 --> 00:56:46,319
I told you I'd heard that before.

850
00:56:47,862 --> 00:56:50,365
Now we have a sentence translated,

851
00:56:50,448 --> 00:56:52,593
and we can use that to figure out
what all of this means.

852
00:56:52,617 --> 00:56:54,553
I mean, Reed could build
an algorithm, and then...

853
00:56:54,577 --> 00:56:57,205
His big brain is busy. I'm all over this.

854
00:56:57,289 --> 00:57:01,543
A Rosetta stone to find him
an Archimedes lever.

855
00:57:02,210 --> 00:57:03,336
See?

856
00:57:03,420 --> 00:57:05,213
I can reference old stuff too.

857
00:57:11,219 --> 00:57:14,306
Right. There you go. Good boy.

858
00:57:33,201 --> 00:57:34,953
<i>Fantastic Four has verified</i>

859
00:57:35,036 --> 00:57:38,456
<i>that an unknown spacecraft
believed to be Galactus</i>

860
00:57:38,539 --> 00:57:40,458
<i>has just passed Jupiter.</i>

861
00:57:40,541 --> 00:57:42,835
<i>Financial</i>
<i>institutions remain closed</i>

862
00:57:42,918 --> 00:57:44,795
<i>as angry protestors take to...</i>

863
00:57:44,878 --> 00:57:47,465
<i> The newly formed</i>
<i>Galactus cult intends</i>

864
00:57:47,548 --> 00:57:48,841
<i>to summit Mount Everest.</i>

865
00:57:49,425 --> 00:57:52,636
<i> Tempers boiled over</i>
<i>in Central London today,</i>

866
00:57:52,720 --> 00:57:56,765
<i>breaking out in violence
as the whole world wonders,</i>

867
00:57:56,849 --> 00:57:59,102
<i>"What is to be our fate?"</i>

868
00:58:01,270 --> 00:58:02,981
Hey, what about us?

869
00:58:03,982 --> 00:58:05,274
We got families too.

870
00:58:06,650 --> 00:58:08,861
Guys, it's getting bad out there.

871
00:58:09,445 --> 00:58:12,698
<i>It seems to me</i>
<i>they have no plan for Galactus.</i>

872
00:58:12,781 --> 00:58:15,409
<i>We, as a society,
have to reckon with the idea</i>

873
00:58:15,493 --> 00:58:18,246
<i>that the Fantastic Four
could save us today,</i>

874
00:58:18,329 --> 00:58:20,498
<i>- but they choose not to?</i>
<i>- No.</i>

875
00:58:20,581 --> 00:58:22,583
<i>The idea is simple.</i>

876
00:58:22,666 --> 00:58:25,711
<i>Reed Richards and Sue Storm
hand over their baby,</i>

877
00:58:25,794 --> 00:58:26,879
<i>and we all live.</i>

878
00:58:26,962 --> 00:58:28,422
<i>One life...</i>

879
00:58:36,014 --> 00:58:38,182
Where are you?

880
00:58:38,266 --> 00:58:40,101
Get down from your high tower.

881
00:58:42,936 --> 00:58:45,356
You're supposed to protect us.

882
00:58:45,439 --> 00:58:46,774
Give up the baby!

883
00:58:49,818 --> 00:58:52,280
- They're scared.
- Who isn't scared?

884
00:58:52,363 --> 00:58:55,116
That is scary.

885
00:58:55,199 --> 00:58:57,660
Why? They can't hurt us.

886
00:58:57,743 --> 00:58:59,495
Well, it's scary because they hate us.

887
00:58:59,578 --> 00:59:01,556
They think they might die,
and they hate us for it.

888
00:59:01,580 --> 00:59:02,998
And they hate Franklin.

889
00:59:04,417 --> 00:59:05,251
And they may be right

890
00:59:05,334 --> 00:59:07,586
because right now,
we don't have a workable plan.

891
00:59:07,670 --> 00:59:09,172
The clock is ticking.

892
00:59:09,255 --> 00:59:10,631
So their plan looks good.

893
00:59:10,714 --> 00:59:13,134
It's mathematical, it's ethical

894
00:59:13,217 --> 00:59:15,803
and it's available.

895
00:59:17,263 --> 00:59:18,514
What are you saying?

896
00:59:19,390 --> 00:59:23,352
I'm not saying anything.

897
00:59:37,032 --> 00:59:39,243
Oh, sweetheart. It's all right, buddy.

898
00:59:41,454 --> 00:59:42,996
All right.

899
00:59:45,583 --> 00:59:47,042
You know, Ben's wrong.

900
00:59:47,835 --> 00:59:49,545
There's always people that can hurt you.

901
00:59:50,963 --> 00:59:52,881
Sue, please hear me.

902
00:59:53,841 --> 00:59:55,360
I would never give him up to Galactus.

903
00:59:55,384 --> 00:59:56,427
I would never do that.

904
00:59:56,510 --> 00:59:59,097
"Mathematical? Ethical? Available?"

905
00:59:59,180 --> 01:00:00,931
It was just so easy for you to say that.

906
01:00:01,014 --> 01:00:02,015
It means nothing.

907
01:00:02,100 --> 01:00:04,102
It means I know you.
I know how your brain works.

908
01:00:04,185 --> 01:00:05,519
It means you've thought about it.

909
01:00:05,603 --> 01:00:08,457
It means you've rolled it around
in your head, and you worked the problem.

910
01:00:08,481 --> 01:00:09,690
Which means nothing.

911
01:00:10,691 --> 01:00:13,819
It is my job to think terrible things
so that terrible things don't happen.

912
01:00:13,902 --> 01:00:15,028
It's not your job, Reed.

913
01:00:15,654 --> 01:00:16,655
That's you.

914
01:00:17,448 --> 01:00:19,992
Okay. You're right, it is me.

915
01:00:21,785 --> 01:00:23,871
I don't dream. I don't wonder.

916
01:00:24,372 --> 01:00:27,958
I invite the worst
possible thing into my head

917
01:00:28,542 --> 01:00:31,962
to figure out how to hurt them
before they hurt anybody else.

918
01:00:32,045 --> 01:00:33,339
And you know what? Sometimes…

919
01:00:33,422 --> 01:00:36,675
Sometimes, you being you hurts me.

920
01:00:40,429 --> 01:00:41,680
Well, I don't mean to.

921
01:00:47,060 --> 01:00:48,396
I know. I know.

922
01:00:48,479 --> 01:00:51,857
I know.

923
01:00:54,026 --> 01:00:55,361
Listen, I am going to solve this.

924
01:00:55,444 --> 01:00:56,779
I'm gonna make it right.

925
01:01:03,744 --> 01:01:05,704
Hmm.

926
01:01:06,997 --> 01:01:10,751
We don't know what he is
or what he might become…

927
01:01:13,003 --> 01:01:15,256
But I am not giving him up.

928
01:01:37,695 --> 01:01:39,822
You're selfish.

929
01:01:46,870 --> 01:01:48,914
How can you bring him out here?

930
01:01:50,165 --> 01:01:51,959
I wanted to introduce you to someone.

931
01:01:53,919 --> 01:01:56,505
This is our son, Franklin.

932
01:01:57,506 --> 01:01:59,300
There's been a lot of talk about him.

933
01:02:01,802 --> 01:02:02,803
Um...

934
01:02:05,223 --> 01:02:08,392
Most of you know me.
You know my story.

935
01:02:08,476 --> 01:02:11,312
When Johnny and I were kids,
our parents were in a car crash.

936
01:02:12,730 --> 01:02:15,524
Our dad was driving and he lived,

937
01:02:16,442 --> 01:02:18,068
but our mom didn't.

938
01:02:18,611 --> 01:02:21,822
<i>I know what it's like to be part
of a family that was torn apart.</i>

939
01:02:23,241 --> 01:02:26,244
<i>Our dad, he wasn't always a great father,
but he wanted to be.</i>

940
01:02:26,327 --> 01:02:27,495
He did his best.

941
01:02:27,578 --> 01:02:30,998
He wanted us to be together
because that's what family is.

942
01:02:31,915 --> 01:02:34,668
It's about fighting for something
bigger than yourself.

943
01:02:35,461 --> 01:02:38,171
It's about connecting to something
bigger than yourself.

944
01:02:57,650 --> 01:03:00,319
It's about having something
bigger than yourself.

945
01:03:01,236 --> 01:03:02,530
And the four of us...

946
01:03:02,613 --> 01:03:05,408
the four of us already do
because we have you.

947
01:03:08,786 --> 01:03:10,413
You know, our mom always used to say,

948
01:03:10,496 --> 01:03:13,999
"Suzie, for you, I would
move heaven and earth."

949
01:03:15,959 --> 01:03:18,086
And we would do that for you.

950
01:03:22,300 --> 01:03:25,928
I will not sacrifice my child
for this world.

951
01:03:28,431 --> 01:03:31,600
But I will not sacrifice
this world for my child.

952
01:03:35,771 --> 01:03:37,440
We will face this together.

953
01:03:38,357 --> 01:03:40,192
We will fight this together.

954
01:03:40,734 --> 01:03:42,528
And we will defeat this together.

955
01:03:43,321 --> 01:03:44,530
As a family.

956
01:03:49,952 --> 01:03:50,953
Mmm.

957
01:03:51,036 --> 01:03:53,539
"As a family."

958
01:03:55,916 --> 01:03:57,084
Archimedes.

959
01:03:58,836 --> 01:03:59,920
The Law of Levers.

960
01:04:00,003 --> 01:04:02,715
"Give me a lever and a place to stand
and I will move the earth."

961
01:04:02,798 --> 01:04:05,258
We are going to move heaven and earth.

962
01:04:06,969 --> 01:04:08,303
Well, just earth.

963
01:04:08,971 --> 01:04:09,972
Sue?

964
01:04:11,724 --> 01:04:12,725
You solved it.

965
01:04:12,808 --> 01:04:13,809
I did?

966
01:04:13,892 --> 01:04:16,395
Yes. We are going to move Earth

967
01:04:16,479 --> 01:04:19,147
to a place that Galactus
will never find us.

968
01:04:19,815 --> 01:04:20,816
How?

969
01:04:21,484 --> 01:04:23,611
Well, we already have the lever.

970
01:04:23,694 --> 01:04:24,862
The bridge.

971
01:04:24,945 --> 01:04:26,530
The bridge is a prototype.

972
01:04:26,614 --> 01:04:29,950
You moved an egg across the room.
You think you can do that with a planet?

973
01:04:30,033 --> 01:04:31,194
We are out of options.

974
01:04:31,243 --> 01:04:33,537
We have to make it work.
We will make it work.

975
01:04:35,789 --> 01:04:36,999
Heaven and earth.

976
01:04:43,005 --> 01:04:44,399
<i>We interrupt this program</i>

977
01:04:44,423 --> 01:04:45,424
<i>with a special report.</i>

978
01:04:45,508 --> 01:04:47,426
<i>And now an announcement
from Reed Richards.</i>

979
01:04:47,510 --> 01:04:48,594
As you're about to see,

980
01:04:48,677 --> 01:04:50,596
we've solved the physics of teleportation.

981
01:04:57,185 --> 01:04:58,646
H.E.R.B.I.E.

982
01:05:00,648 --> 01:05:03,066
The difference between a planet
and an egg is only scale.

983
01:05:04,735 --> 01:05:06,194
<i>Starting immediately,</i>

984
01:05:06,278 --> 01:05:09,156
<i>we will create teleportation bridges
spanning the globe.</i>

985
01:05:09,239 --> 01:05:11,742
<i>They will be synchronized
and interconnected,</i>

986
01:05:11,825 --> 01:05:14,745
<i>capable of transporting our planet
to a new solar system</i>

987
01:05:14,828 --> 01:05:17,415
<i>within a 2% margin
of the inhabitable zone.</i>

988
01:05:18,081 --> 01:05:20,751
<i>But more importantly,
away from Galactus</i>

989
01:05:20,834 --> 01:05:23,336
<i>where he won't be able
to find us for millions of years.</i>

990
01:05:23,421 --> 01:05:25,297
Time is not on our side.

991
01:05:25,380 --> 01:05:27,591
I'm reaching out to the world
with a list of materials

992
01:05:27,675 --> 01:05:29,176
that we need in bulk.

993
01:05:29,259 --> 01:05:31,178
Plutonium-239.

994
01:05:31,261 --> 01:05:33,431
Plutonium...

995
01:05:33,514 --> 01:05:34,640
All right, people.

996
01:05:34,723 --> 01:05:36,183
Like my old man used to say,

997
01:05:36,266 --> 01:05:38,686
"If you don't know what to do,
pick up a shovel."

998
01:05:38,769 --> 01:05:41,313
Fire it up.
We got bridges to build. Let's go.

999
01:05:46,485 --> 01:05:50,197
<i>The last 36 hours has seen
an historical mobilization</i>

1000
01:05:50,280 --> 01:05:52,825
<i>of every country working together,</i>

1001
01:05:52,908 --> 01:05:55,368
<i>in a way the world has never seen before.</i>

1002
01:05:59,915 --> 01:06:03,001
<i>With Galactus's ship</i>
<i>deep within our solar system</i>

1003
01:06:03,085 --> 01:06:05,838
<i>and the Fantastic Four's Hail Mary
in the balance,</i>

1004
01:06:06,505 --> 01:06:09,049
<i>we are calling on every helping hand.</i>

1005
01:06:09,132 --> 01:06:10,843
<i>If you can do something well,</i>

1006
01:06:10,926 --> 01:06:12,511
<i>now you can do it for your planet.</i>

1007
01:06:20,352 --> 01:06:24,272
<i>We are getting reports</i>
<i>that Galactus has passed Mars.</i>

1008
01:06:26,692 --> 01:06:27,818
H.E.R.B.I.E., record.

1009
01:06:36,326 --> 01:06:37,745
It takes too much power.

1010
01:06:39,079 --> 01:06:41,540
I only got this to work
by tripling my intake,

1011
01:06:41,624 --> 01:06:43,602
which drained the New York City grid
in two seconds.

1012
01:06:43,626 --> 01:06:45,919
To do this, there isn't enough
power in the world.

1013
01:06:46,003 --> 01:06:48,255
I'd have to turn off
every light switch on the planet.

1014
01:06:49,715 --> 01:06:50,716
For how long?

1015
01:06:51,925 --> 01:06:54,177
Factoring in we gotta
keep building bridges,

1016
01:06:54,261 --> 01:06:57,180
how long would we need
to conserve power?

1017
01:06:58,807 --> 01:07:00,392
<i>Sacrifices will be made.</i>

1018
01:07:01,143 --> 01:07:04,021
We all need to conserve power
at a scale never attempted before.

1019
01:07:04,104 --> 01:07:06,481
Quite right, H.E.R.B.I.E.

1020
01:07:06,565 --> 01:07:08,817
All the power.

1021
01:07:09,652 --> 01:07:11,820
<i>The worldwide energy curfew only works</i>

1022
01:07:11,904 --> 01:07:14,281
<i>if everybody does their part
to conserve electricity.</i>

1023
01:07:19,494 --> 01:07:21,705
Ooh, missed a spot.

1024
01:07:21,789 --> 01:07:24,291
Yeah, curfew fried it.

1025
01:07:24,374 --> 01:07:25,876
Now I look like an idiot.

1026
01:07:28,295 --> 01:07:29,337
Beard could be cool.

1027
01:07:31,048 --> 01:07:32,049
Seriously?

1028
01:07:33,592 --> 01:07:35,468
I built this to see what you looked like.

1029
01:07:36,720 --> 01:07:37,721
You see,

1030
01:07:38,513 --> 01:07:41,767
most fathers want their sons
to look exactly like them,

1031
01:07:42,643 --> 01:07:43,936
inside and out.

1032
01:07:44,978 --> 01:07:45,979
But...

1033
01:07:47,439 --> 01:07:48,941
I don't want you to be like me.

1034
01:07:52,402 --> 01:07:54,780
There's something wrong with me,
always has been.

1035
01:07:59,451 --> 01:08:00,911
The more I look at you,

1036
01:08:02,788 --> 01:08:04,081
the less I know.

1037
01:08:05,373 --> 01:08:07,542
And the less I know, the more scared I am.

1038
01:08:09,878 --> 01:08:13,131
So you know what?
I'm not gonna look anymore.

1039
01:08:16,093 --> 01:08:18,470
I'm gonna let you tell me who you are.

1040
01:08:18,553 --> 01:08:21,348
And if you'd like to tell me now,
that would be helpful,

1041
01:08:21,431 --> 01:08:24,392
especially if you're
an all-powerful space god.

1042
01:08:24,476 --> 01:08:27,771
I'd like to know that sooner
rather than later, if you don't mind.

1043
01:08:30,691 --> 01:08:31,984
Hmm.

1044
01:08:32,067 --> 01:08:33,736
Oh, no.

1045
01:08:33,819 --> 01:08:35,445
You're busy peeing.

1046
01:08:36,739 --> 01:08:38,031
You're a very good boy.

1047
01:08:47,750 --> 01:08:49,835
Thanks, buddy.

1048
01:08:55,382 --> 01:08:57,300
This is going to work.

1049
01:08:58,886 --> 01:08:59,887
It has to.

1050
01:09:32,836 --> 01:09:35,047
Yes! Yes!

1051
01:09:35,923 --> 01:09:37,883
Uh... Oh.

1052
01:09:37,966 --> 01:09:39,760
Yep, coming. Coming, coming, coming.

1053
01:09:41,053 --> 01:09:44,347
Guys, I am onto something.

1054
01:09:44,431 --> 01:09:45,808
Moving a planet here, Johnny.

1055
01:09:45,891 --> 01:09:48,977
Yeah, Johnny. It's four. Fantastic Four.

1056
01:09:49,061 --> 01:09:50,270
Let's move a planet.

1057
01:09:50,353 --> 01:09:52,605
- Cool beard.
- You mean that? Thank you.

1058
01:09:53,857 --> 01:09:55,525
Copy, Delhi.

1059
01:09:56,443 --> 01:09:57,503
<i>Let's do this.</i>

1060
01:09:57,527 --> 01:09:58,528
<i>London, stand by.</i>

1061
01:09:58,570 --> 01:09:59,822
Yes, copy, London.

1062
01:10:01,281 --> 01:10:02,365
Copy, Paris.

1063
01:10:02,449 --> 01:10:05,035
- Lima, do you copy?
- Copy, Rome.

1064
01:10:05,118 --> 01:10:07,370
- Copy, Delhi.
- Copy, Vienna.

1065
01:10:07,454 --> 01:10:08,747
Copy, Prague.

1066
01:10:08,831 --> 01:10:10,224
<i>Chicago, stand by.</i>

1067
01:10:10,248 --> 01:10:11,541
Copy, Chicago.

1068
01:10:12,835 --> 01:10:14,211
Earth go for countdown.

1069
01:10:15,087 --> 01:10:16,797
<i>Here we go, folks.</i>

1070
01:10:16,880 --> 01:10:18,548
Go.

1071
01:10:18,631 --> 01:10:21,593
<i>20, 19...</i>

1072
01:10:22,302 --> 01:10:26,306
<i>18, 17, 16...</i>

1073
01:10:27,224 --> 01:10:31,937
<i>15, 14, 13...</i>

1074
01:10:32,687 --> 01:10:34,314
<i>12...</i>

1075
01:10:34,397 --> 01:10:36,066
<i>11...</i>

1076
01:10:36,149 --> 01:10:40,237
<i>10, 9, 8...</i>

1077
01:10:40,320 --> 01:10:43,115
<i>7, 6...</i>

1078
01:10:44,116 --> 01:10:45,784
- What is that?
- What's happening?

1079
01:11:12,019 --> 01:11:14,396
- She's going for this bridge.
- No.

1080
01:11:15,647 --> 01:11:16,857
She's coming for Franklin.

1081
01:11:18,650 --> 01:11:20,778
- Oh, my God.
- Lock the building down!

1082
01:11:22,821 --> 01:11:25,365
Wait. Where's Johnny?

1083
01:11:55,979 --> 01:11:57,772
<i>- Shalla-Bal.
- Shalla-Bal.</i>

1084
01:11:57,856 --> 01:11:58,857
<i>Shalla-Bal!</i>

1085
01:12:15,665 --> 01:12:17,587
You understand these messages...

1086
01:12:18,961 --> 01:12:20,838
You know my language?

1087
01:12:21,671 --> 01:12:23,673
I've learned about you.

1088
01:12:25,758 --> 01:12:26,759
Shalla-Bal.

1089
01:12:28,846 --> 01:12:31,014
How do you know that name?

1090
01:12:31,098 --> 01:12:33,100
And how did you get these?

1091
01:12:34,226 --> 01:12:36,228
Die with yours.

1092
01:12:36,311 --> 01:12:37,604
How?

1093
01:12:37,687 --> 01:12:39,647
He barely has a grasp
of the English language.

1094
01:12:39,731 --> 01:12:42,067
Twenty-three transmissions,

1095
01:12:42,150 --> 01:12:43,818
all in your language,

1096
01:12:44,486 --> 01:12:47,155
trace back to the planet Zenn-La.

1097
01:12:48,156 --> 01:12:50,283
Your home.

1098
01:12:52,494 --> 01:12:55,080
They were looking for you, to thank you.

1099
01:12:56,164 --> 01:12:58,291
Once I translated one phrase,

1100
01:12:59,167 --> 01:13:00,878
I pieced together enough language

1101
01:13:00,961 --> 01:13:03,671
to understand a part of your history.

1102
01:13:04,714 --> 01:13:08,676
<i>You were some sort of
scientist or astronomer.</i>

1103
01:13:10,137 --> 01:13:12,931
<i>When Galactus came,
you offered to serve as his scout</i>

1104
01:13:13,015 --> 01:13:14,432
<i>if he'd spare your planet.</i>

1105
01:13:15,600 --> 01:13:17,978
<i>Was it to spare your family?</i>

1106
01:13:40,250 --> 01:13:42,169
<i>He turned you into this.</i>

1107
01:13:46,214 --> 01:13:47,215
<i>Shalla-Bal.</i>

1108
01:13:48,550 --> 01:13:52,512
Those were messages
from the one planet Galactus spared.

1109
01:13:52,595 --> 01:13:53,972
Your planet.

1110
01:13:56,141 --> 01:13:58,351
These planets weren't so lucky.

1111
01:14:01,396 --> 01:14:03,690
How many
do you remember, Shalla-Bal?

1112
01:14:03,773 --> 01:14:07,485
Proxima Delphi. Saigas.

1113
01:14:07,569 --> 01:14:08,987
Do you remember Polaris?

1114
01:14:11,198 --> 01:14:15,118
They begged for mercy.

1115
01:14:15,202 --> 01:14:18,621
You brought Galactus
to all of these planets.

1116
01:14:18,705 --> 01:14:21,749
And now you're bringing him here,

1117
01:14:21,833 --> 01:14:24,877
to my home, to my family!

1118
01:14:42,812 --> 01:14:44,772
Just trying to save my world, you know,

1119
01:14:46,358 --> 01:14:47,525
like you did.

1120
01:14:52,697 --> 01:14:54,282
So give up the child.

1121
01:14:54,907 --> 01:14:57,869
If he was older, he would do it himself.

1122
01:14:59,371 --> 01:15:00,372
Like I did.

1123
01:15:01,206 --> 01:15:02,665
So take me.

1124
01:15:04,876 --> 01:15:06,461
Take me.

1125
01:15:06,544 --> 01:15:07,712
Not the boy.

1126
01:15:09,547 --> 01:15:12,050
Let me make the sacrifice.

1127
01:15:13,385 --> 01:15:15,220
It's not yours to make.

1128
01:15:15,928 --> 01:15:17,680
Then stay and help us.

1129
01:15:19,141 --> 01:15:20,433
There is no help.

1130
01:15:22,519 --> 01:15:25,397
Take the child
and leave this doomed place.

1131
01:15:26,814 --> 01:15:29,359
Maybe you'll live long enough
to forgive yourselves.

1132
01:15:39,036 --> 01:15:41,829
- Johnny, that was incredible.
- I mean, does it even matter?

1133
01:15:41,913 --> 01:15:43,123
You saved Franklin.

1134
01:15:43,790 --> 01:15:44,957
Yes, it matters.

1135
01:15:45,042 --> 01:15:46,126
Reed?

1136
01:15:47,752 --> 01:15:48,878
We're not leaving, are we?

1137
01:15:49,754 --> 01:15:51,423
No. No, we're not.

1138
01:15:54,717 --> 01:15:55,802
We're not leaving.

1139
01:16:02,850 --> 01:16:05,520
Um... Uh, yeah. Same here.

1140
01:16:05,603 --> 01:16:07,105
You gotta give us a second. Um...

1141
01:16:07,189 --> 01:16:09,066
Yeah, this is Johnny Storm.
Can you hear me?

1142
01:16:09,149 --> 01:16:10,751
The line's too busy.

1143
01:16:10,775 --> 01:16:12,044
- I'm sorry, okay?
<i>- This is London.</i>

1144
01:16:12,069 --> 01:16:14,404
<i>- This is London. Do you copy?</i>
- Hold, London.

1145
01:16:14,487 --> 01:16:16,329
<i>What's going on?</i>

1146
01:16:17,949 --> 01:16:19,909
Hold, Paris. Paris, hold.

1147
01:16:19,992 --> 01:16:21,137
The line's not very clear.

1148
01:16:21,161 --> 01:16:22,962
- Can you say that again?
- Hold the line.

1149
01:16:23,871 --> 01:16:25,332
Chicago, yes, we're onto it.

1150
01:16:25,415 --> 01:16:27,584
We're just, uh... We're fixing the problem.

1151
01:16:32,046 --> 01:16:34,729
We're trying to get, uh...
We're trying to get on top of this.

1152
01:16:34,799 --> 01:16:36,319
- Sydney, stand by.
- Yep. Got it.

1153
01:16:36,343 --> 01:16:38,720
- Tokyo, stand by.
- Hold. Hold.

1154
01:16:38,803 --> 01:16:40,388
We have to bring him here.

1155
01:16:40,472 --> 01:16:42,890
- We are aware.
- Yes, I understand.

1156
01:16:42,974 --> 01:16:45,059
- Can you stand by?
- We are aware.

1157
01:16:45,143 --> 01:16:48,020
- I'll update you.
- Yeah. Yeah.

1158
01:16:48,563 --> 01:16:50,523
We need to bring Galactus here.

1159
01:16:50,607 --> 01:16:52,692
I will come back to you. Hold.

1160
01:16:52,775 --> 01:16:53,985
- Call you back.
- Hold up.

1161
01:16:54,527 --> 01:16:55,528
Reed?

1162
01:16:56,113 --> 01:16:58,030
We need Galactus to come here?

1163
01:16:58,115 --> 01:17:00,926
I feel like we just spent a lot of time
trying to prevent that from happening.

1164
01:17:00,950 --> 01:17:02,970
Listen to me. We need to
get him away from his ship.

1165
01:17:02,994 --> 01:17:05,955
We need to bring him here,
to Times Square.

1166
01:17:06,038 --> 01:17:07,039
And then what?

1167
01:17:07,081 --> 01:17:10,668
And then, instead of moving
a planet away from one giant...

1168
01:17:11,211 --> 01:17:13,671
we move one giant
away from the planet.

1169
01:17:13,755 --> 01:17:17,300
If we route every power grid
on the Eastern Seaboard,

1170
01:17:17,384 --> 01:17:21,012
through our one last bridge,
charge back up,

1171
01:17:21,554 --> 01:17:25,142
we can keep the portal open for...

1172
01:17:34,484 --> 01:17:35,610
Thirty-seven seconds.

1173
01:17:35,693 --> 01:17:38,405
Thirty... Not a lot of time

1174
01:17:38,488 --> 01:17:40,282
to throw a space god off a planet.

1175
01:17:40,365 --> 01:17:42,575
- No, it is not.
- And where do we send him?

1176
01:17:43,117 --> 01:17:44,452
To the far edges of the universe.

1177
01:17:44,536 --> 01:17:46,037
Without a ship, he'll be stranded.

1178
01:17:46,120 --> 01:17:48,206
How are we supposed to get Galactus
to Times Square?

1179
01:17:48,290 --> 01:17:51,543
And how do we move one giant
through one large bridge?

1180
01:17:55,129 --> 01:17:57,006
I haven't figured that part out yet.

1181
01:18:01,052 --> 01:18:02,136
You have.

1182
01:18:03,095 --> 01:18:04,138
Have what?

1183
01:18:04,847 --> 01:18:06,891
We have to use the only thing
Galactus wants.

1184
01:18:06,974 --> 01:18:08,685
No. I'll think of another way.

1185
01:18:08,768 --> 01:18:10,204
- What are you talking about?
- You can't.

1186
01:18:10,228 --> 01:18:11,414
You can't think of another way.

1187
01:18:11,438 --> 01:18:13,064
- I will.
- There is only one way.

1188
01:18:13,147 --> 01:18:14,482
What are you talking about?

1189
01:18:16,818 --> 01:18:18,486
We have to use Franklin.

1190
01:18:21,364 --> 01:18:22,365
Yes.

1191
01:18:22,949 --> 01:18:24,075
You wanna use the boy?

1192
01:18:27,829 --> 01:18:29,664
You wanna use the boy as bait.

1193
01:18:29,747 --> 01:18:31,583
- No.
- That's your plan?

1194
01:18:31,666 --> 01:18:33,626
No, it's not my plan. It's our plan.

1195
01:18:33,710 --> 01:18:35,212
It's the only plan.

1196
01:18:35,295 --> 01:18:36,647
It's not my plan. I hate that plan.

1197
01:18:36,671 --> 01:18:38,816
- It's a bad plan. Stupid plan.
- Terrible idea.

1198
01:18:38,840 --> 01:18:42,260
Why don't I just burn through his ship?
That's another plan.

1199
01:18:42,344 --> 01:18:43,487
He's your kid we're talking about.

1200
01:18:43,511 --> 01:18:44,637
Sue.

1201
01:18:45,179 --> 01:18:47,056
- I know.
- Sue. Sue.

1202
01:18:47,139 --> 01:18:48,933
Yes, I know. I know. I know!

1203
01:19:18,004 --> 01:19:21,383
I thought this was one of
the most beautiful things we'd ever built.

1204
01:19:23,885 --> 01:19:25,428
Feels terrifying now.

1205
01:19:27,138 --> 01:19:28,848
It can be beautiful again.

1206
01:19:30,433 --> 01:19:31,768
Everything can.

1207
01:19:40,777 --> 01:19:43,321
They've been gone a while.

1208
01:19:45,365 --> 01:19:46,366
Johnny.

1209
01:19:47,284 --> 01:19:48,485
Go check. See if they're back.

1210
01:19:48,535 --> 01:19:51,413
I'm in no rush to do that.

1211
01:19:52,204 --> 01:19:53,686
Well, I'm definitely not gonna check.

1212
01:19:53,748 --> 01:19:55,333
I'm definitely not going either.

1213
01:19:55,417 --> 01:19:56,685
Thank you for going and checking.

1214
01:19:56,709 --> 01:19:57,853
You're welcome. It's the least I could do

1215
01:19:57,877 --> 01:19:59,313
to say thank you
for going down to check first.

1216
01:19:59,337 --> 01:20:00,797
I'm definitely not going down.

1217
01:20:00,880 --> 01:20:02,632
- Chickenshits.
- Jesus.

1218
01:20:02,715 --> 01:20:03,841
Don't do that.

1219
01:20:03,925 --> 01:20:05,528
- I hate it when you do that.
- Don't do that.

1220
01:20:05,552 --> 01:20:08,137
Come on. Let's run through the details.

1221
01:20:09,972 --> 01:20:11,724
I don't like when she does that.

1222
01:20:11,808 --> 01:20:12,809
It's like...

1223
01:20:12,892 --> 01:20:15,770
It's unsettling when people
just appear like that.

1224
01:20:17,855 --> 01:20:20,191
Bombproof. Shockproof.

1225
01:20:21,192 --> 01:20:22,610
Radiation-proof.

1226
01:20:26,406 --> 01:20:28,741
Franklin will go here
when Galactus arrives.

1227
01:20:30,242 --> 01:20:33,496
Hey, do we know what direction
Galactus will be coming from?

1228
01:20:34,914 --> 01:20:36,183
Well, it could be from anywhere.

1229
01:20:36,207 --> 01:20:39,752
But when he crosses those lines,
we trigger it.

1230
01:20:41,921 --> 01:20:44,424
We're in
the very center of the city.

1231
01:20:44,507 --> 01:20:47,677
We're surrounded by
miles of apartment buildings.

1232
01:20:48,595 --> 01:20:50,638
Any path he takes,
he's gonna be going through

1233
01:20:50,722 --> 01:20:52,974
thousands and thousands of families.

1234
01:20:54,726 --> 01:20:56,436
I got an idea you'll hate.

1235
01:20:59,481 --> 01:21:02,191
Oh, my.

1236
01:21:02,274 --> 01:21:03,943
Very advanced.

1237
01:21:04,026 --> 01:21:08,155
So this must be where the sausage is made.

1238
01:21:09,532 --> 01:21:12,034
I think I prefer just trying
to steal the sausage.

1239
01:21:12,118 --> 01:21:13,495
Please, don't touch.

1240
01:21:14,621 --> 01:21:15,622
Oh!

1241
01:21:16,163 --> 01:21:17,164
We'll fix that.

1242
01:21:17,206 --> 01:21:18,416
The...

1243
01:21:18,500 --> 01:21:19,751
Harvey.

1244
01:21:19,834 --> 01:21:22,003
Hello there, little robot man.

1245
01:21:22,587 --> 01:21:24,422
Could you dim the lights for me, please?

1246
01:21:26,591 --> 01:21:29,469
Harvey, we wanted to ask you something.

1247
01:21:29,552 --> 01:21:33,180
And whatever it is,
I would like him to ask me.

1248
01:21:33,264 --> 01:21:35,975
It's not... It's not Reed or me asking.

1249
01:21:36,058 --> 01:21:37,685
It's the entire planet asking.

1250
01:21:37,769 --> 01:21:39,538
It wouldn't be the entire planet now,
would it?

1251
01:21:39,562 --> 01:21:40,397
Just the over part.

1252
01:21:40,480 --> 01:21:42,565
No, Mr. Elder. We've met Galactus.

1253
01:21:42,649 --> 01:21:44,025
He'll eat the under part first.

1254
01:21:44,108 --> 01:21:48,237
Well, regardless,
why don't you butter me up?

1255
01:21:51,449 --> 01:21:52,534
Spread it on.

1256
01:21:52,617 --> 01:21:54,869
- Okay, Mole Man.
- Mole Man?

1257
01:21:54,952 --> 01:21:55,870
You touch another piece of my...

1258
01:21:55,953 --> 01:21:57,473
- Enough.
- Take the "mole" out of it.

1259
01:21:57,497 --> 01:21:58,766
- It's Mr. Elder to you.
- That is enough.

1260
01:21:58,790 --> 01:22:00,792
Give us a minute. Just give us a minute.

1261
01:22:00,875 --> 01:22:03,210
Yes, that's it.

1262
01:22:03,294 --> 01:22:05,630
Johnny, don't be mad.
I didn't dress you.

1263
01:22:05,713 --> 01:22:07,465
Don't listen to him.
You're handsome.

1264
01:22:08,841 --> 01:22:09,967
Harvey.

1265
01:22:10,051 --> 01:22:11,886
I'm sorry, Sue. I'm...

1266
01:22:12,720 --> 01:22:14,180
End of days.

1267
01:22:14,263 --> 01:22:16,516
We all gotta learn how to laugh.

1268
01:22:17,349 --> 01:22:18,976
So what do you need?

1269
01:22:19,894 --> 01:22:23,397
<i>Evacuation orders are</i>
<i>in effect in the Greater New York area.</i>

1270
01:22:23,481 --> 01:22:25,149
<i>Please report to Subterranea.</i>

1271
01:22:26,150 --> 01:22:29,737
<i>Evacuation orders are in effect
in the Greater New York area.</i>

1272
01:22:29,821 --> 01:22:31,864
<i>Please report to Subterranea.</i>

1273
01:22:38,705 --> 01:22:41,415
Welcome to Subterranea.

